==English==

===Pronunciation===
* [[IPA]] /'dεðmætč/

===Etymology===
Presumably first used in id® Software's Doom®, which used the word to present an available style of networked game play. Networked games were very uncommon (if existant at all) before Doom®, which brought first person shooters into the limelight in becoming a vastly popular game.

===Etymology===
The term was originally coined by [[w:John Romero|John Romero]] in 1993 during the development of ''[[w:Doom|Doom]]''.
===Noun===
# A computer game mode found in [[first-person shooter]]s, in which the players are not on teams and try to [[frag]] as many other players as possible.

===Verb===
# Play a deathmatch.